
[1]malicious

   MALI'CIOUS, a. Harboring ill will or enmity without provocation;
   malevolent in the extreme; malignant in heart.

   I grant him bloody,

   Sudden, malicious, smacking of every sin

   That has a name.

   1. Proceeding from extreme hatred or ill will; dictated by malice; as a
   malicious report.
